		(layer "F.Cu")
		(uuid "5bcdc23b-0ba6-421b-9022-e08abc598443")
		(at 76 43.27)
		(descr "Samtec MCX-J-P-X-ST-SM1 straight surface-mount MCX jack, 50 ohm. Land pattern per the datasheet RECOMMENDED PCB LAYOUT (docs/datasheets/mcx-j-p-x-st-mt1-mkt.pdf, rev C): centre signal pad Ø1.65, four square ground pads 2.10x2.10 on a 6.54 mm square pitch (centres at +/-3.27, +/-3.27 = the body corners). Body square 5.88 mm (corners reach Ø8.32), mating barrel Ø4.50, height 6.00, cable exits straight up. Ground pads share a net so neighbouring ground pads may overlap. Pad 1 = centre signal, pad 2 = ground (shell). Ground pads sit at the corners, so the signal trace escapes on a cardinal axis between them (no 45 deg connector rotation needed). NOTE: mated MCX cable plugs are ~Ø8 mm coupling envelope -- at this pitch they cannot all sit side-by-side, so cable access is staggered.")
